Subject: Typescript from Steve

Hey try running this typescript for your project, I think it will help streamline it. Let me know if there are bugs!


import nodemailer from "nodemailer";

const transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({ sendmail: true });

transporter.sendMail({
  from: "me@example.com",
  to: "contact@contact.com",
  subject: "",
  text: "confirmation"
});

Subject: C# Email Snippet Fix

You had some issues instantiating the SMTP client — here's a corrected version: using System.Net.Mail;

MailMessage mail = new MailMessage("me@example.com", "contact@contact.com");
mail.Body = "confirmation";

SmtpClient client = new SmtpClient();
client.Send(mail);

Subject: Java for your project

Was thinking more about the issues you were having with your project, and wrote up this java for you. Lemme know if there any bugs. Hope it helps!

import javax.mail.*;
import javax.mail.internet.*;

public class EmailSender {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        MimeMessage msg = new MimeMessage(Session.getDefaultInstance(System.getProperties()));
        msg.setFrom("me@example.com");
        msg.addRecipient(Message.RecipientType.TO, new InternetAddress("contact@contact.com"));
        msg.setText("confirmation");
        Transport.send(msg);
    }
}

